Replace Your Technology Habit with Healthier Choices Kindle Edition

by Everett Smith (Author), Turner Mcnamee (Editor) Format: Kindle Edition
5.0 out of 5 stars 2 ratings
See all formats and editions
  • Kindle
    $0.00     Read with Kindle Unlimited to also enjoy access to over 1 million more titles $2.99 to buy
Most of us can probably agree that we spend 3 or more hours every day on electronics.


Now, spending a few hours on electronics once a week is ok, but spending 5 to 6 hours hours on average everyday has been scientifically proven to cause physical and mental damage to the human body.


I guarantee that after reading this article, you will attempt to limit your habit of being on technology as much but it is your choice to follow through.


Today Im going to talk about all the bad scenarios that can occur when playing on your electronics for more than 4 hours everyday. We are also going to be discussing how to get away from spending so much time on technology and start making healthier choices.




The Consequences of Overusing Technology


If you keep using technology over 4 hours every day there will be consequences and these consequences could last for your entire life.


These consequences can be:
Brain Restructuring
Eye strain
Text Neck
Moody
